extends layout.pug

block content 
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro
    div

      //- Add a title or heading like My Portfolio, or Hey, Potential Employers, or Let's make the web great together! 
      h1 My JavaScript Portfolio

      //- Add a description for your portfolio, what this project is, it's purpose, what it's supposed to accomplish, etc. 
      p.lead.text-light
        | This is a portfolio of my JavaScript projects. Currently these are all projects that I've completed
        | as part of the Treehouse (teamtreehouse.com) Full Stack JavaScript Techdegree program. I'm completing
        | this program to freshen my coding skills after a 12-year coding vacation, and I'm having a great
        | time!
  article.grid-container.portfolio-index
    
    .grid-x.grid-margin-x.small-up-2.medium-up-2.large-up-3

      //- Use the Pug `each` iterator to create a project img, title and link 
      //- in the markup for each of the projects you are showcasing.  
      each project in projects
        //- Use a combination of interpolation and template literals as needed to dynamically 
        //- generate the routes in the href, as well as the img's src and the projects title.
        
        //- Here's what the Pug for each project example should look like. 

        .cell
          a(href='#{id}')
            img.thumbnail(src='#{image_urls[0]}')
            h5= project_name
      
